Products.description:
Buyers who purchased this product via DropX will be able to list for sale on November 29th, 2020 at 12:00 PM ET.
Following the successful Initial Product Offering of last years 2019 release, StockX and Topps are back at it again for another exclusive release: The 2020 Bowman Chrome X. The release includes a 100 player checklist, with Green X-Fractor Base Cards numbered /31, Gold X-Fractors numbered /3, and a 1/1 Red X-Fractor Parallel for each player. Each box will include, one graded prospect or rookie card numbered to /31 (Green X-Fractor), /3 (Gold X-Fractor), or 1/1 (Red X-Fractor). Each card will already be graded and slabbed by PSA.
Similar to last year, the Green X-Fractor parallels are exclusive to this 2020 Bowman Chrome X release, which can only be bought via this DropX. There are only 1,000 boxes and 500 cases available via this DropX, so secure your 2020 Bowman Chrome X box today and hit that Buy Now button above.
Click here to see the PSA pop reports for all of the rookies in the set. Click here to see the PSA pop reports for all prospects in the set.
For this exclusive DropX, Asks are ascending, so buy early for the lowest prices! $5 shipping, 3% processing fee, and sales tax not included in the Lowest Ask price.

Products.description: The 2020 Topps Chrome Ben Baller Baseball set brings baseball card collectors a collaborationn between world-famous jewler, artist, musician and actor, Ben Baller. Products.description: The Kevin Durant 2007-08 Topps Rookie #2, while not KD's true Topps base rookie, is a notable and unique card. This card, with white borders, could only be bought as part of an exclusive 14-card rookie set of the 2007 NBA Draft class which also included Greg Oden, Al Horford, Mike Conley, and Joakim Noah. Over his career with the Oklahoma City Thunder and Golden State Warriors, Durant has met and exceeded expectations winning Rookie of the Year, MVP, multiple NBA titles, and just a few Finals MVP honors. The former Texas Longhorn will look to build on that resume, teaming up with Kyrie Irving as part of the Brooklyn Nets.
Products.name: Rookie #2
Products.title: Kevin Durant 2007 Topps Rookie #2
